Subject: RE: Engine cutting out

After checking all of the wires, contacts and vacuum hoses recommended by
the group I began experimenting to find out if I could cause or work around
the issue.
This is what I've come up with...
I start the bus and when I let go of the ignition she stalls.
I've found that if I get her started, turn to off the back to the on
position quick enough she will run.  It takes several attempts sometimes but
I think I've isolated the issue to the ignition switch.  I don't know why
she sometimes quits enroute but maybe the spring back mech in the switch
releases.  I've limited my key ring for the bus to one key since I found out
the weight of many keys can wear out an ignition switch.
I'll have to read some archives as I think the 71 may be a one year only
switch and requires some extra wiring.
Thanks for all the suggestions. 

Oly Olsen
Great Falls Montana
'71 Riviera
